#### What is the problem you are having with rclone?
Broken "Following symbolic links" SSH remote -> Cache remote -> Mount.

#### What is your rclone version (eg output from `rclone -V`)
rclone v1.39-251-g0a0318dfÎ²
- os/arch: linux/amd64
- go version: go1.10


#### Which OS you are using and how many bits (eg Windows 7, 64 bit)
Ubuntu 16.04.04 64bit

####  Which cloud storage system are you using? (eg Google Drive)
SSH

#### The command you were trying to run (eg `rclone copy /tmp remote:tmp`)
1. Set the ssh (sftp) remote
2. make a cache remote of SFTP (CRANsvc)
3. mount with ```/usr/bin/rclone mount CRANsvc:cransvc /mnt/cransvc -L --allow-other --allow-non-empty --transfers 128 --cache-workers 128 --checkers 256 --cache-db-purge --fast-list -vv --dump headers &> /var/log/rclone.txt &```
4. Try to open https://cran.asia/bin/macosx/R-3.4.4.pkg
